  "summaries": [
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":1,"summary":"Solomon worships at Gibeon, asks God for wisdom rather than riches, and is granted both wisdom and unparalleled wealth."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":2,"summary":"Solomon communicates with Huram king of Tyre to obtain materials and skilled craftsmen for building the temple."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":3,"summary":"Construction of the temple begins on Mount Moriah with elaborate detail of the holy place, the most holy place, and the cherubim."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":4,"summary":"The temple furnishings are described: the brasen altar, molten sea, lavers, candlesticks, tables, and courts."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":5,"summary":"The Ark of the Covenant is brought into the temple; the glory of the Lord fills the house in a cloud as the musicians praise."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":6,"summary":"Solomon delivers a blessing and dedicatory prayer, petitioning God to hear prayers offered toward the temple in various circumstances."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":7,"summary":"Fire from heaven consumes the offering; God appears to Solomon by night with promises of blessing for obedience and warnings for apostasy."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":8,"summary":"Solomon builds cities, organizes labor, and establishes regular worship at the temple according to the law of Moses."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":9,"summary":"The Queen of Sheba visits Solomon and is overwhelmed by his wisdom and wealth; Solomon's glory and riches are detailed."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":10,"summary":"Rehoboam rejects the counsel of the elders and harshly answers the people, causing the ten northern tribes to revolt."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":11,"summary":"Rehoboam is forbidden from fighting Israel; he fortifies Judah's cities and the Levites and faithful Israelites gather to him."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":12,"summary":"Rehoboam and Judah forsake the Lord; Shishak of Egypt invades; the king humbles himself and receives partial deliverance."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":13,"summary":"Abijah rebukes Jeroboam's apostasy, declares Judah's faithfulness to the Levitical priesthood, and wins a great battle through divine aid."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":14,"summary":"Asa removes idolatry from Judah, builds fortified cities, and defeats the massive Ethiopian army through prayer and divine intervention."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":15,"summary":"The prophet Azariah encourages Asa; the king removes abominations and renews the covenant, and the people seek God wholeheartedly."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":16,"summary":"Asa makes an alliance with Syria against Israel instead of trusting God; the seer Hanani rebukes him; Asa ends his reign in anger and disease."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":17,"summary":"Jehoshaphat walks faithfully, sends princes and Levites to teach the law throughout Judah, and the surrounding nations fear him."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":18,"summary":"Jehoshaphat joins Ahab against Ramoth-gilead despite Micaiah's warning of disaster; Ahab is killed in battle as prophesied."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":19,"summary":"Jehu rebukes Jehoshaphat for his alliance with Ahab; the king appoints judges and charges them to act faithfully in the fear of the Lord."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":20,"summary":"Facing a vast enemy coalition, Jehoshaphat leads Judah in fasting and prayer; God sends a miraculous victory as the singers praise."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":21,"summary":"Jehoram kills his brothers, follows Ahab's wicked ways, receives Elijah's written rebuke, and dies of a terrible disease without honor."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":22,"summary":"Ahaziah reigns wickedly under Athaliah's counsel; he is slain by Jehu; Athaliah seizes the throne and destroys the royal seed except Joash."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":23,"summary":"Jehoiada the priest leads a coup to crown the young prince Joash, executes Athaliah, and renews the covenant between God and the people."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":24,"summary":"Joash repairs the temple under Jehoiada's guidance but after Jehoiada's death turns to idolatry and murders the prophet Zechariah."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":25,"summary":"Amaziah defeats Edom but foolishly worships their gods; he challenges Israel, is defeated, and is eventually assassinated."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":26,"summary":"Uzziah prospers greatly as long as he seeks God but is struck with leprosy for presumptuously burning incense in the temple."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":27,"summary":"Jotham reigns righteously, builds the upper gate of the temple, defeats the Ammonites, and prospers because he walks steadfastly before the Lord."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":28,"summary":"Ahaz practices extreme idolatry including child sacrifice; Judah suffers devastating defeats from Syria, Israel, Edom, and the Philistines."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":29,"summary":"Hezekiah reopens and cleanses the temple in his first month as king, restoring Levitical worship and sacrificial offerings with great joy."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":30,"summary":"Hezekiah invites all Israel and Judah to keep the Passover in Jerusalem; God heals those who sought Him despite imperfect ceremonial preparation."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":31,"summary":"The people destroy idols throughout the land and generously contribute tithes and offerings to support the priests and Levites."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":32,"summary":"Sennacherib invades Judah; Hezekiah fortifies Jerusalem and trusts God; an angel destroys the Assyrian army; Hezekiah's later pride is noted."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":33,"summary":"Manasseh's extreme wickedness leads to captivity; he repents in prison and is restored, then removes idols and rebuilds the altar."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":34,"summary":"Young Josiah purges the land of idolatry, discovers the Book of the Law during temple repairs, and leads a national covenant renewal."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":35,"summary":"Josiah keeps the greatest Passover since Samuel; he tragically dies in battle against Pharaoh Necho at Megiddo."},
    {"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":36,"summary":"The last four kings of Judah reign in wickedness; Jerusalem is destroyed; the people are exiled to Babylon; Cyrus decrees their return."}
  ],
